comments: Sabonis (SAC) jumps alongside Oubre Jr. (CHA) and marginal contact occurs during Oubre Jr.'s driving shot attempt.
Replay review of the out-of-bounds called on Sabonis (SAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Plumlee (CHA) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Plumlee (CHA) is moving laterally when he makes leg to leg contact with Fox (SAC), which affects his SQBR during the driving shot attempt.
Fox (SAC) initiates contact with Hayward (CHA) off ball that affects his ability to set the screen.
Hayward (CHA) is late to establish himself in Mitchell's (SAC) path and does not give him room to avoid the contact during the pick.
Oubre Jr. (CHA) retracts his arm from Fox's (SAC) path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Fox (SAC) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as he defends Hayward (CHA) during the drive.
Sabonis (SAC) extends his arm out and marginal contact occurs with Hayward's (CHA) arm.
Oubre Jr. (CHA) grazes the ball and marginal follow-through arm contact occurs with Mitchell (SAC) during the steal attempt on the perimeter.
Ball (CHA) moves alongside Fox's (SAC) path and maintains a legal guarding position as incidental contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Fox (SAC) jumps into and makes contact with Oubre Jr.'s (CHA) body, which dislodges him after he secures the rebound.
Plumlee (CHA) and Sabonis (SAC) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Murray (SAC) cleanly deflects Oubre Jr.'s (CHA) pass and is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Huerter (SAC) extends his leg out and makes intentional foot to ball contact.
During the inbound, Murray (SAC) mutually engages and disengages with Washington (CHA) as he makes clean contact with the ball to deflect it away.

Sabonis (SAC) and Plumlee (CHA) mutually engage and immediately disengage as Sabonis makes clean contact with the ball to dislodge the rebound. Any follow-through contact after the dislodge is deemed incidental.

Replay review of the foul called on Ball (CHA) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Ball (CHA) swipes down and initiates contact with Fox's (SAC) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Hayward (CHA) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Fox's (SAC) arm before he cleanly gathers the ball at the end of his drive.
Plumlee (CHA) legally contests and avoids contact with Fox (SAC) during the driving shot attempt.
Fox (SAC) moves slightly toward Oubre Jr. (CHA) and marginal contact occurs during the pass.
Murray (SAC) and Washington (CHA) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Huerter (SAC) commits a take foul on Maledon (CHA).
Oubre Jr. (CHA) legally contests Fox's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Fox (SAC) jumps into and initiates contact with Maledon's (CHA) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Plumlee (CHA) and Washington (CHA) legally contests Huerter's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
